We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

(45) record the transaction/ event at real-time and  (46) use the appropriate accounting entries;
(47) recognize the receipt of goods from the supplier with the appropriate inventory account and (48) record the issuance of inventories to the end-users using the appropriate expense account based on the SSMI prepared by the designated General Services Officer.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor provide the necessary assistance to the Municipal Treasurer, in terms of manpower, in order to intensify and maximize collection of Real Property/Special Education Taxes.

Likewise, we recommended that the Municipal Treasurer perform the ff:
1. Develop an effective Tax Collection Campaign program to intensify and maximize collection of Real Property/Special Education Tax Receivables;
2. Deputize the Barangay Treasurers, in addition to the collectors of the LGU to collect all taxes on real property located in the Barangay, provided that the Barangay Treasurer is properly bonded for the purpose. Collection and remittance of RPT by Barangay Treasurer be closely monitored by the Municipal Treasurer.
3. Issue a notice of delinquency to each concerned property owner and post the same at the main entrance of the Municipal Hall and in a publicly accessible and conspicuous place in each Barangay of the Local Government Unit of Javier;
4. Prepare a certified list of all real property tax delinquencies which remained uncollected or unpaid for at least one (1) year, and a statement of the reason or reasons for such non-collection or non-payment, and submit the same to the Sanggunian concerned on or before December thirty-first (31st) of the year immediately succeeding the year in which the delinquencies were incurred, with a request for assistance in the enforcement of the remedies for collection either by administrative action thru levy on real property or by judicial action;
We also recommended that the Municipal Assessor conduct inventory and appraisal of properties that are subject to Real Property Tax and provide a report to the Accounting Office as basis of recording Real Property/Special Education Tax Receivables.
